Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with distinct cathode materials usually differ in output performance.
Titulo: Contribution of properties of composite cathode and cathode/electrolyte interface to cell performance in a planar solid oxide fuel cell stack

Sentencas: In this study, 2 mu m-thick Pt voltage probes are embedded into the cathode/electrolyte interface.
Titulo: Contribution of properties of composite cathode and cathode/electrolyte interface to cell performance in a planar solid oxide fuel cell stack

Sentencas: The effects of the electrical properties and cathode/electrolyte interfaces of LSCF-GDC and LSM-YSZ composite cathodes on cell performance are investigated in situ for anode-supported planar SOFCs.
Titulo: Contribution of properties of composite cathode and cathode/electrolyte interface to cell performance in a planar solid oxide fuel cell stack

Sentencas: Results show that the voltage and maximum output power density measured by the probes on both sides of the LSCF-GDC and LSM-YSZ composite cathodes are 7% and 4%, respectively, of those of the corresponding cell during instantaneous current voltage testing.
Titulo: Contribution of properties of composite cathode and cathode/electrolyte interface to cell performance in a planar solid oxide fuel cell stack

Sentencas: The enhanced LSCF cell performance is mainly attributed to the rough GDC/LSCF-GDC interface that is responsible for the three-dimensional contact between the GDC layer and LSCF-GDC cathode particles and increases the triple-phase boundary (TPB) length.
Titulo: Contribution of properties of composite cathode and cathode/electrolyte interface to cell performance in a planar solid oxide fuel cell stack

Sentencas: The LSM-YSZ cathode performance degradation is attributed to the variation in polarization resistance caused by cathode particle growth.
Titulo: Contribution of properties of composite cathode and cathode/electrolyte interface to cell performance in a planar solid oxide fuel cell stack

Sentencas: However, the primary factor for the degradation of LSCF-GDC cathode performance is structural instability, such as inner cracks.
Titulo: Contribution of properties of composite cathode and cathode/electrolyte interface to cell performance in a planar solid oxide fuel cell stack
